.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-installed \- List **every installed package** (via your native package manager and every
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility installed
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
List **every installed package** (via your native package manager and every
.SH WHAT IT DETECTS
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBSystem managers:\fP apt, dnf, yum, zypper, pacman, apk, xbps, eopkg,
  emerge, brew, macports, nix, guix
.IP \(bu 4
\fBApp stores:\fP snap, flatpak, chocolatey, scoop, winget
.IP \(bu 4
\fBLanguage ecosystems:\fP pip, pipx, npm, pnpm, yarn, bun, gem, cargo,
  rustup, go, composer, conda, uv, dotnet, luarocks, opam, tlmgr
.IP \(bu 4
\fBTools / plugins:\fP asdf, gh extensions, kubectl krew
.PP
Package detection is best-effort: if a manager's list command is unavailable
or errors out, it is skipped silently. The \fC$PATH\fP scan walks every directory
in \fC$PATH\fP, collects executable files, de-duplicates by basename, and sorts.
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash main.sh installed                 # packages + PATH commands (default)
bash main.sh installed --packages      # only package managers
bash main.sh installed --commands      # only PATH executables
bash main.sh installed --all --count   # counts only
bash main.sh installed --category language
bash main.sh installed --manager apt,brew,npm
bash main.sh installed --json          # machine-readable summary
bash main.sh installed --export report.txt
.EE
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Flag   |   Description
\fC--packages\fP   |   List installed packages per detected manager
\fC--commands\fP   |   List every executable found in \fC$PATH\fP
\fC--all\fP   |   Both (default)
\fC--category c1,c2\fP   |   Filter: \fCsystem\fP, \fCapps\fP, \fClanguage\fP, \fCtools\fP
\fC--manager id1,id2\fP   |   Only these manager ids
\fC--count\fP   |   Show counts instead of full names
\fC--json\fP   |   Emit a JSON summary
\fC--export FILE\fP   |   Write a plain-text report to \fCFILE\fP
\fC--no-color\fP   |   Disable ANSI colors
.PP
.SH OUTPUT FORMAT
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
While each manager's list command runs, a \fBlive spinner\fP (\fC◐ ◓ ◑ ◒\fP on
  UTF-8 terminals, \fC| / - \\fP otherwise) shows next to \fCQuerying <manager>\fP. The
  spinner is disabled automatically when output is not a TTY or when using
  \fC--json\fP / \fC--export\fP, so machine-readable output stays clean.
.IP \(bu 4
Each detected package is printed as:
.PP
  ```
  [ - name → vX ]
  ```
.PP
  The version is \fBforced to a \fCv\fP prefix\fP (\fC1:2.3.4\fP becomes \fCv1:2.3.4\fP). When
  a manager reports no version (e.g. go binaries, rustup toolchains, asdf
  plugins, gh/krew extensions) only the name is shown:
.PP
  ```
  [ - name ]
  ```
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fC--json\fP emits \fC{"name","version"}\fP objects per manager (version is \fC""\fP when
  unknown).
.PP
.SH NOTES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
Read-only: the tool never installs, removes, or modifies anything.
.IP \(bu 4
Output degrades gracefully: colors are stripped when piped or with \fCNO_COLOR\fP.
